{"id":4754,"date":"2024-01-14T06:33:18","date_gmt":"2020-01-14T01:03:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=4754"},"modified":"2024-10-26T19:29:53","modified_gmt":"2024-10-26T13:59:53","slug":"indian-style-bedroom-designs","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/indian-style-bedroom-designs\/","title":{"rendered":"Love Detail And Deep Sleep? You Need These Indian Style Bedroom Designs Right Now!"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>A compilation of cherry-picked Indian bedroom designs crafted to spellbind that fuzzy mind.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You\u2019re lying if you say your bedroom isn\u2019t your most loved place to be no matter where you are currently. Social media has literally given birth to a whole new Relationship Status: In a committed relationship with my bed. Preposterous? We think smart. It\u2019s only the sole room in your home that you feel most cosy and private. All that reading, me time, thinking, over-thinking (if we may say so) and everyone\u2019s favourite &#8211; sleeping!. All of it happens within the confines of the four walls of this comforting paradise. Seems ludicrous to not want to pay special attention to every detail of your personal cocoon, of sorts, right?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Do you know why Indian style bedroom designs won\u2019t ever be edged out by even all that speaks vogue? It\u2019s because of the immense warmth added by each of these bedroom designs that make it feel like home. This isn\u2019t to say they aren\u2019t savvy. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/bedroom-design\/\">Bedroom interior designs<\/a> in India have seen avant-garde do-overs and how! We\u2019re here to show you, quite literally, just that.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">All That Glitters Is Not Gold<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The interiors of an Indian Bedroom are simply incomplete without hints of royalty that accentuate traditional looking antique furniture. If you\u2019re going <em>au traditionnel<\/em>, make sure to incorporate stunning copper or gold backdrops to flame your bedroom game. Gold might seem like a tacky option for some, so copper seems like the more popular choice when it comes to Indian bedroom designs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002448\/indian-bedroom-designs-copper-dark-brown.jpg\" alt=\"Indian bedroom designs with stunning copper or gold backdrops to flame your bedroom design in india\" class=\"wp-image-4756\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002448\/indian-bedroom-designs-copper-dark-brown.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002448\/indian-bedroom-designs-copper-dark-brown-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002448\/indian-bedroom-designs-copper-dark-brown-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002448\/indian-bedroom-designs-copper-dark-brown-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Hints of copper and dark brown taking finesse to a whole other level<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Classic Black And White<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Ever wondered how the two most basic colours come together to make a bold statement? Black and white Indian bedroom designs are a popular choice in modern-day interior designs and mighty rightfully so. An all-white bedroom interior? Meh. Throw in a few black elements? You\u2019re suddenly going to feel like the likes of Downy Jr\u2019s bedroom. It\u2019s fascinating how the colours of some elements can literally transform your entire bedroom design, isn\u2019t it?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002452\/classic-modern-black-white-indian-style-bedroom-design.jpg\" alt=\"Classic modern black and white indian style bedroom designs are a popular choice in modern-day bedroom interior designs\" class=\"wp-image-4757\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002452\/classic-modern-black-white-indian-style-bedroom-design.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002452\/classic-modern-black-white-indian-style-bedroom-design-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002452\/classic-modern-black-white-indian-style-bedroom-design-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002452\/classic-modern-black-white-indian-style-bedroom-design-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A classic modern monochrome Indian-style bedroom design that boasts all things classy<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Interior designs for a traditional indian home\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/26183536\/traditional-indian-home-interior-designs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Dressy Backsplashes<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Looking to spruce up your existing bedroom? All you need is a single bold element to break the monotony of a boring room. Vivacious backsplashes are an excellent way to complement an all-white bedroom interior. Small spaces in particular, that struggle with re-decoration can make use of an all-white airy atmosphere with ample light coming in and large mirrors that reflect light, for a spacious look. To maintain this clutter-free zone, a single charmer, like a patterned backsplash positioned right behind your bed looks effortlessly beautiful.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002456\/bedroom-design-indian-grey-white-backsplash.jpg\" alt=\"Bedroom design indian with an eccentric grey white backsplash that makes beautiful master bedroom designs india\" class=\"wp-image-4758\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002456\/bedroom-design-indian-grey-white-backsplash.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002456\/bedroom-design-indian-grey-white-backsplash-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002456\/bedroom-design-indian-grey-white-backsplash-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002456\/bedroom-design-indian-grey-white-backsplash-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">An eccentric grey-white backsplash that makes this Indian-style bedroom an artistic paradise<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Layer Me Good<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Nothing says snug like layering up. For an elegant and cosy bedroom, aim to use warm shades of pink, grey or blue along with white. You can even layer up with stacked comforters and cushioned satin pillows to complete this warm and fuzzy bedroom design. A small Indian bedroom has more potential to re-create than you would assume. Warm wooden floors and dim-lit hanging pendant lights are going to transform your room to make you feel all things snug!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002459\/bedroom-designs-indian-style-soft-colours-piled-up-pillows.jpg\" alt=\"Bedroom designs indian style with soft colours and piled up pillows make an elegant and cosy indian bedroom\" class=\"wp-image-4759\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002459\/bedroom-designs-indian-style-soft-colours-piled-up-pillows.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002459\/bedroom-designs-indian-style-soft-colours-piled-up-pillows-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002459\/bedroom-designs-indian-style-soft-colours-piled-up-pillows-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002459\/bedroom-designs-indian-style-soft-colours-piled-up-pillows-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A fabric play amidst soft colours and piled up pillows make this Indian-style bedroom the ideal cosy corner<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Hang Me Low<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>An age-old trick but one that\u2019s sure to work is a stout bed. Or no bed at all. Many modern bedroom designs practically have just about an inch-high wooden platform and a slender mattress layered up well. Who knew fancying up would mean cutting down? (On cost and space, how about that?)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002503\/bedroom-designs-india-low-lying-bed-frame.jpg\" alt=\"Bedroom designs india with a low lying bed frame against a pop of tangerine\" class=\"wp-image-4760\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002503\/bedroom-designs-india-low-lying-bed-frame.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002503\/bedroom-designs-india-low-lying-bed-frame-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002503\/bedroom-designs-india-low-lying-bed-frame-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002503\/bedroom-designs-india-low-lying-bed-frame-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A low lying bed frame against a pop of tangerine that makes the bedroom seem spacious and bright<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Vibrant Colours<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A traditional Indian bedroom generally boasts antique furniture that blends in well within a mix of bold colours and ethnic prints. Not only do colourful elements make your private cocoon stand out from the rest of your home, but it also makes your Indian bedroom look mighty swank!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002507\/indian-style-bedroom-interior-bold-colours-ethnic-prints.jpg\" alt=\"Indian style bedroom interior design with a mix of bold colours and ethnic prints\" class=\"wp-image-4761\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002507\/indian-style-bedroom-interior-bold-colours-ethnic-prints.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002507\/indian-style-bedroom-interior-bold-colours-ethnic-prints-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002507\/indian-style-bedroom-interior-bold-colours-ethnic-prints-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002507\/indian-style-bedroom-interior-bold-colours-ethnic-prints-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Smart use of bolder colours that make this Indian-style bedroom appear mighty grand<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">A Warm Summer\u2019s Day<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Every day is a vacation day when your Indian style bedroom looks tropical. Spice things up a notch with groovy green wallpapers and large airy windows that make your bedroom glow! Another way to give your Indian bedroom a tropical makeover is using a colour palette limited to shades of blue, copper and white. Add a few turquoise and white throw pillows with a bamboo ottoman and your room is sure to take you back to the ocean.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002511\/indian-style-bedroom-groovy-green-wallpapers.jpg\" alt=\"Indian style bedroom designs with a groovy green wallpapers and large airy windows to make marvellous bedroom design in india\" class=\"wp-image-4762\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002511\/indian-style-bedroom-groovy-green-wallpapers.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002511\/indian-style-bedroom-groovy-green-wallpapers-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002511\/indian-style-bedroom-groovy-green-wallpapers-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002511\/indian-style-bedroom-groovy-green-wallpapers-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Warm Wood And Snug Sheets<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Cosy is an unsaid bedroom theme and quite a favourite, too! Warm wood against white backdrops create a winter vibe the best. It needs no additional accessorising besides a soft rug and a minimalistic bedside table. Besides, who wouldn\u2019t fancy a bedroom that boasts an atmosphere of healing, ailment and all things Christmas?!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002514\/bedroom-designs-india-low-cost-wooden-flooring-brick-walls.jpg\" alt=\"Bedroom designs india with low cost by using combination of wooden flooring and brick walls\" class=\"wp-image-4763\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002514\/bedroom-designs-india-low-cost-wooden-flooring-brick-walls.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002514\/bedroom-designs-india-low-cost-wooden-flooring-brick-walls-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002514\/bedroom-designs-india-low-cost-wooden-flooring-brick-walls-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/21002514\/bedroom-designs-india-low-cost-wooden-flooring-brick-walls-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A combination of wooden flooring, brick walls and a restricted palette of off-whites makes this bedroom design all things homey<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now you have it at your fingertips &#8211; Indian style bedroom designs to rock the inner <em>desi <\/em>in you. For everyone out there looking for that Indian touch this is your go-to list!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore, More About<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/almirah-designs-for-indian-bedroom\/\">Almirah Designs For Indian Bedroom<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/indian-style-living-room-designs\/\">Indian Style Living Room Designs<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/space-saving-furniture-small-indian-homes\/\">Space Saving Furniture Designs For Small In